# Known divergence: unsupported bind-parameter expression. NOT a multigres
# behavioral bug in the raster code. This test invokes a non-volatile function
# whose body performs DROP TABLE; on stock PostgreSQL the statement reaches the
# backend and PostgreSQL rejects it with "DROP TABLE is not allowed in a
# non-volatile function". multigres rejects the same statement earlier: the call
# passes a non-literal (a FuncCall) as a bind parameter, and multigateway only
# supports literal parameter values, so it returns "parameter 1: unsupported
# expression type *ast.FuncCall; only literal values are supported". Both are
# errors on the same statement and every other line is byte-identical; only this
# rejection's wording differs, so it is recorded here as an accepted divergence.
--- a
+++ b
@@ -24,7 +24,7 @@
 T12|t|t|t|t
 ERROR: INSERT is not allowed in a non-volatile function
 ERROR: COPY is not allowed in a non-volatile function
-ERROR: DROP TABLE is not allowed in a non-volatile function
+ERROR: parameter 1: unsupported expression type *ast.FuncCall; only literal values are supported
 T15|t
 0|1|INTERSECTION|0.000|0.000|2|2|1.000|1.000|0.000|0.000|0|1|32BF|0.000|1.000|1.000
 0|2|INTERSECTION|1.000|-1.000|1|2|1.000|1.000|0.000|0.000|0|1|32BF|0.000|1.000|1.000
